Event: Using Generative AI Video for Marketing (w BMS + AIC)
Event Description:
Video has become the backbone of modern marketing—and with generative AI, creating high-quality, tailored content is faster and smarter than ever. Join The Generator, Babson Marketing Society, and AI Club for a hands-on event exploring how AI is transforming marketing workflows.

We’ll dive into the newest platforms and techniques shaping the field:

Opus: streamline editing and repurposing video content in seconds.

Arcads: generate fresh video campaigns with minimal lift.

n8n Automations: connect AI-generated scripts, voiceovers, and editing tools into seamless pipelines.

From social media campaigns to brand storytelling, discover how marketers are using generative AI to scale ideas, save time, and unlock creativity. Whether you’re building a personal brand, leading a student org, or eyeing a career in marketing, this event will give you an insider’s look at the future of video-first strategy.

Event Description:
Not all AI tools are created equal. Some drive productivity, some fuel creativity—and some cross the line. In this interactive event, The Generator spotlights Cluely AI, a tool built to “do the work for you,” and challenges Babson students to think critically about what happens when innovation drifts into academic dishonesty.

Through live demos and head-to-head activities, you’ll see how Cluely integrates into everyday workflows and test for yourself whether speed and automation can replace effort and learning. Then, we’ll flip the script: how might tools like this be reimagined for ethical use?

Join us for a hands-on conversation about the gray areas of AI adoption—where efficiency ends, and responsibility begins.

Looking to spark new connections at Babson? The Generator, in collaboration with POW, invites you to an evening of AI-powered matchmaking with a twist. Forget swiping—this event pairs you with peers based on real compatibility scores. Whether you’re here to meet a potential date, expand your circle of friends, or just have a laugh at the results, this experience blends technology with a touch of campus intrigue.

Each participant will be matched into small groups, with one pairing flagged as your highest “compatibility match.” Expect icebreakers, conversation prompts, and a lighthearted atmosphere designed to take the pressure off while letting AI do the behind-the-scenes magic.

The AI Coding Tools Workshop, in collaboration with CODE, will be a student-led event focused on exploring AI-driven software development tools, specifically highlighting platforms such as Cursor, lovable, Replit Agent, Windsurf, Claude Code, and many more. Student facilitators will lead interactive sessions, showcasing how to build ready MVPs that are AI-powered code generation and how to  debug. The event will emphasize practical applications, collaborative learning, and engagement through live demos and Q&A.

Competitions will span disciplines, from technical sprints to creative showcases:

Coding Golf: precision problem-solving in as few lines as possible.

Design + Creativity Challenges: from AI-generated campaigns to rapid prototyping.

Wildcard Events: sports analytics, data visualization relays, and surprise prompt engineering comp.

Event: Friendgroup MatchMaking with AI (Web app leading up to 10/17)
Event Description:
Powering this event is The Generator’s custom-built matchmaking webapp—a tool that blends personality profiling, interest-mapping, and behavioral pattern recognition to connect Babson students in fresh ways. Here’s how it works:

Compatibility Scoring: AI models analyze participant inputs to create ranked match lists.

Dynamic Grouping: Matches aren’t one-on-one alone; groups are created to spark both friendships and chemistry.

Date Match Highlight: Each group includes one “highlighted match,” a potential spark revealed in real time at the event.

The goal isn’t just romance—it’s about creating genuine connections across campus using AI in a way that’s both social and a little bit daring.
